ZH: 我们应该提倡储蓄的习惯。
EN: We should promote the habit of savings.

ZH: 她把每个月的薪水一部分用于储蓄。
EN: She puts a portion of her monthly salary into savings.

ZH: 他们正在努力增加他们的储蓄。
EN: They are working hard to increase their savings.

ZH: 储蓄可以为将来的教育做准备。
EN: Savings can be used for future education.

ZH: 储蓄能帮助我们应对紧急情况。
EN: Savings can help us deal with emergencies.

ZH: 这笔钱将被储蓄用于购买房屋。
EN: This money will be saved for buying a house.

ZH: 她总是很节俭地进行储蓄。
EN: She always saves money very thriftily.

ZH: 存款帮助您开始储蓄。
EN: Deposits help you start saving.

ZH: 他们计划将储蓄用于旅行。
EN: They plan to use their savings for travel.

ZH: 她有一个储蓄账户来存放她的钱。
EN: She has a savings account to store her money.

ZH: 别忘了把一部分工资存入储蓄账户。
EN: Don't forget to put some of your salary into your savings account.

ZH: 经济危机敦促人们更多地进行储蓄。
EN: Economic crises urge people to save more.

ZH: 她储蓄用于未来子女的教育。
EN: She saves for her children's future education.

ZH: 我们家庭的长期目标是增加储蓄。
EN: The long-term goal of our family is to increase savings.

ZH: 他们每个月把一部分钱存入储蓄账户。
EN: They deposit a portion of their money into savings account every month.

ZH: 在农村，人们通常有土地储蓄的习惯。
EN: In rural areas, people usually have the habit of land savings.

ZH: 储蓄可以为创业提供资金支持。
EN: Savings can provide financial support for entrepreneurship.

ZH: 很多人认为储蓄是经济独立的基础。
EN: Many people believe that savings is the foundation of financial independence.

ZH: 持续进行储蓄是一个良好的生活方式。
EN: Consistent savings is a good lifestyle.

ZH: 我们决定储蓄以备不时之需。
EN: We decided to save for a rainy day.
